    "instruction": "Load metric.csv, trace.csv, log.csv, and error_logs.csv. Parse the timestamp columns as UTC datetimes. For each of the three normalized numeric files (metric, trace, log) aggregate by (cmdb_id, KPI-name) where KPI-name is kpi_name for metric, trace_name for trace, and log_name for log. For each aggregated series compute: count of points, earliest timestamp, latest timestamp, global P95 of value, and global P5 of value. Return up to the top 50 rows sorted by count descending for each file in compact tabular form with columns: source_file, cmdb_id, kpi_name, count, earliest_ts, latest_ts, p95, p5. For error_logs.csv return a compact summary: distinct cmdb_id, count of error messages per cmdb_id, earliest and latest timestamps per cmdb_id, and up to 5 sample messages per cmdb_id. Do not filter by the incident window yet; use full series to calculate thresholds."}

