{
    "analysis": "We parsed anomalous traces into caller/callee pairs. The earliest anomalous traces in the incident window appear at 2024-01-22 09:56:00 UTC and are associated with ts-order-service (a 'from_ts-travel-service' trace recorded at ts-order-service). Multiple ts-order-service trace series show exceedances starting ~09:56–09:59 UTC, while ts-route-service anomalies appear ~10:00 UTC and ts-auth-service anomalies appear later (~10:10–10:15 UTC). Metric anomalies also show that ts-order-service had several KPIs (cpu, diskio, latency, mem, socket, workload) exceeding their global P95 early in the window. To decide the root cause and reason we need to quantify severity: compute how far each metric breach exceeds its global P95 (percent deviation) and rank them, focusing on the earliest anomalies. This will allow identification of the most severe faulty KPI and whether the fault is likely resource-related (CPU, memory, disk I/O, socket) or network-related (latency/packet/socket).",
